r manufacturer behind smith  wesson and rifle manufacturer behind remington in the usa contents  history  facilities  statistics  products  boltaction rifles  singleshot rifles  autoloading rifles  leveraction rifles  shotguns  centerfire pistols  rimfire pistols  doubleaction revolvers  singleaction revolvers  ruger and the usa shooting team  see also  bibliography  references  external links historyedit rugers mk ii  target pistol sturm ruger  company was founded by william b ruger and alexander mccormick sturm in  in a small rented machine shop in southport connecticut just prior to their partnership bill ruger had successfully duplicated two japanese baby nambu pistols in his garage from a captured nambu that he acquired from a returning marine at the close of world war ii when it came to designing their first semiauto pistol ruger decided to incorporate the looks of the german mm luger and the american colt woodsman into their first commercially produced  caliber pistol see ruger standard which became so successful that it launched the entire company ruger is a dominant manufacturer in the  lr rimfire rifle market in the us due primarily to the sales of its ruger  semiautomatic rifle the  is very popular due to being relatively inexpensive and of good quality as a result a wealth of aftermarket accessories and parts were made available for it which has further increased its popularity the availability and variety of aftermarket parts makes it possible to build a  using only these parts most of which are marketed to target shooters and hunters ruger similarly dominates the  rimfire semiautomatic pistol market with the ruger mk ii and ruger mk iii descendants of the ruger standard pistol like the  the mkii is supported with a wide variety of aftermarket accessories the  is similar to the ruger standard family of pistols but features a different grip angle that of the colt  as opposed to that of a luger utilized in the ruger standard ruger casting has plants in newport new hampshire and prescott arizona making ferrous ductile iron and commercial titanium castings ruger golf makes steel and titanium castings for golf clubs made by a number of different brands sturm ruger stock has been publicly traded since  and became a new york stock exchange company in  nysergr after alex sturm’s death in  william b ruger continued to direct the company until his death in  from  through  ruger manufactured over  million firearms and currently offers models for hunting target shooting selfdefense collecting and law enforcement facilitiesedit sturm ruger  co is headquartered in southport connecticut and maintains manufacturing facilities in newport new hampshire prescott arizona and mayodan north carolina rugers subsidiaries are ruger precision metals llc in earth city missouri pine tree castings in newport new hampshire and ruger sportswear  accessories in mayodan north carolina statisticsedit of the total  makers of civilian firearms operating in the united states from – ruger led the industry with  million firearms produced within the period ruger was ranked the number one us firearms manufacturer from – in  ruger manufactured  firearms as their promotion the million gun challenge to benefit the nra played a significant role in the company maintaining its top us manufacturer status the company has set a new goal of  million firearms produced per year from  to  ruger was the topseller of handguns productsedit ruger breaks down their products into nine categories boltaction rifles singleshot rifles autoloading rifles leveraction rifles shotguns centerfire pistols rimfire pistols doubleaction revolvers and singleaction revolvers boltaction riflesedit ruger m mark ii stainless bolt action in  hawkeye m guide gun hawkeye african gunsite scout rifle model  american rifle american rimfire ruger precision rifle singleshot riflesedit no  no  discontinued autoloading riflesedit ruger  stainless with an aftermarket butler creek folding stock and a t